@NODE hist "Changes"




Changes So Far...

------\\
V6.02b |
------/

Found some bugs & fixed them.

------\\
V6.01b |
------/

Changed the return method of Ini_SplitItem

fixed a memhit using Ini_NewItem()

arranged the Autodoc to be in alphabetical order

------\\
V5.02b |
------/

Added command
Ini_SplitItem

------\\
V5.01b |
------/

The DoINI method seemed more effort than it was worth so it's gone again.

Added commands
Ini_RemGroup
Ini_RemItem
Ini_NextGroup
Ini_PrevGroup
Ini_GroupName
Ini_Str2Array
Ini_Array2Str

Added Value.
INIV_Type_Blank

------\\
V4.01b |
------/
Started this guide.

Fixed some mem hits.

------\\
V3.02b |
------/
Completed adding DoINI commands and removed all other functions from
the library

Edited changes to docs
------\\
V3.01b |
------/
Started to add the DoINI() functions

removed mem allocation from Init & removed FreeINI() command
because of wierd happenings with C compilers.
not it is up to the programmer to alloc memory for amigaini object (struct)


------\\
V2.01b |
------/

Can't remember

------\\
V1.01b |
------/

Initial version

@ENDNODE



@NODE back "Background"




amigaini.library was born because the Scalos developement team were
having troubles with a similar library they got from aminet.

the one they had was also pretty big and had way to many features.

so i offered to create a basic ini handling lib for them.



Special Thanks go to ...

Mike Carter (Scalos developement)
  for being the only beta tester.

@ENDNODE


